</td></tr></table><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#484848><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/udamenii.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Damenii</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>議員</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#6F6F6F>9/12/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#6F6F6F>12:04:42 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/fdsafgeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2102.topic&index=2><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Reply</FONT></A></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B>&nbsp<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: RANGER學徒請問: ) </font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial"><br>
Archery in EQ has a lot of limitations when using it and therefore it is not a viable weapon.  Especially when you are in a group fighting, it is very difficult to get a clear shot.  You can level to post 50 with poor archery skill without any problem.  <br>
<br>
Nevertheless, I still practiced archery to the grand master level (200+) for the mere reason that it is the SYMBOL of being a ranger.  In post-50, it is difficult to raise archery skill above 200, unless you have high intelligence.  At that time several hundread arrows of shooting may not raise a skill point at all.<br>
<br>
To get more maximun damage from the bow, you may need to increase strength first.  Dexterity is also important to get fewer miss shots.  And if you want to raise your archery skill quicker, a faster bow is recommended.<br>
<br>
In some dungeons, arrow pulling is very useful to control the crowds when no enchanter or bard is in the group.  For example, in window group of sol B, you can try that strategy to pull only one mob back to your group when you see more than 2 mobs.  Of couse, any melee class who can shoot arrows can use this strategy.  So it is not applicable to ranger only.  However, in the past I usually only saw warrior and ranger prepared the bow and arrows.<br>
<br>
In open field, archery can be a life saver for you and the group.  For example, a puller pulls a small train.  You can kite away some mobs to let your group members concentrate on one or two only.  After they kill the mobs, you can run back to the group and finish the mob(s) you are kiting with your teammmates.  This is the strategy of kiting for protection.</font><P>Dameni SilverKite<BR>

